The Commissioner for Youth and Social Development, Oluwasegun Daodu, has lauded Human Development Initiatives (HDI), a Non-Governmental Organisation, for supporting vulnerable persons in the last 25 years. Daodu, who spoke at HDI’s 25th anniversary, said the government will continue to partner individuals, corporate organisations and other NGOs to provide support for the people. He was represented by Deputy Director, Mrs. Funmilola Peter-Pool. He said: “It is noteworthy to look at the lives you have touched in the last 25 years and feel fulfilled as an organised group of committed individuals…’’   Ohanaeze honours institute’s founder     Sanwo-Olu, Fashola for Traffic Radio’s colloquium     Oyo APC leaders back aspirant   Executive Director of HDI Mrs. Olufunsho Owosanoye noted that the organisation has carried out projects to support its vision, some of which include interventions for widows denied their rights to inheritance, children living with disability, and orphans who cannot afford school, or those on the verge of dropping out…’’ “In commemoration of this silver jubilee, and in furtherance of our vision, we are implementing the HDI IMPACT 25 Project to gift 25 categories of vulnerable persons with 25 impact gift items to alleviate their vulnerabilities…” Some of the HDI Impact 25 project gifts  include 25 tertiary education scholarships for students with disabilities, 25 cane guides for the students of Pacelli school of the blind, 25 hearing aids for pupils in a selected inclusive school, among others.